         determined for you.\n\
        \           \n\
        \            }\n\
        \       {-  You must specify a KMS key ID for [VolumeKmsKeyId] to encrypt the root volume \
         with your own KMS key instead of an Amazon Web Services owned KMS key.\n\
        \           \n\
        \            }\n\
        \       }\n\
        \   Otherwise, by default, the value is [False], and the following applies:\n\
        \   \n\
        \    {ul\n\
        \          {-  The configuration is applied to the secondary volume, while the root volume \
         is encrypted with an Amazon Web Services owned key.\n\
        \              \n\
