        "Specifies whether managed tier checkpointing is enabled or disabled for the HyperPod \
         cluster. When set to [Enable], the system installs a memory management daemon that \
         provides disaggregated memory as a service for checkpoint storage. When set to [Disable], \
         the feature is turned off and the memory management daemon is removed from the cluster.\n"]
}
[@@ocaml.doc
  "Defines the configuration for managed tier checkpointing in a HyperPod cluster. Managed tier \
   checkpointing uses multiple storage tiers, including cluster CPU memory, to provide faster \
   checkpoint operations and improved fault tolerance for large-scale model training. The system \
   automatically saves checkpoints at high frequency to memory and periodically persists them to \
   durable storage, like Amazon S3.\n"]

